'''Ehren Kenneth McGhehey''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɛr|ən|_|m|ə|ˈ|ɡ|iː|h|i}} {{respell|ERR|ən|_|mə|GHEE|hee}}; born November 29, 1976) is an American daredevil and actor. He is best known as one of the stars of the [[MTV]] reality stunt show ''[[Jackass (TV series)|Jackass]]''.
==Jackass== {{Main|Jackass (TV series)}} After McGhehey retired from snowboarding due to injury, he got a job at a skate shop in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]]. There he filmed some of his ideas and stunts on a small scale; he was soon spotted by ''Jackass'' director [[Jeff Tremaine]], who put him on the ''Jackass'' team.<ref name="abc">{{cite web |title=Danger Ehren biodata |url=http://www.dangerehren.com/bio.php |accessdate=2007-06-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070331113247/http://www.dangerehren.com/bio.php |archivedate=2007-03-31 |df= }}</ref>
McGhehey later appeared in all five ''Jackass'' films. Ehren's motto when performing stunts on ''Jackass'' is "Safety First." McGhehey is often referred to by his nickname "Danger Ehren" by fellow ''Jackass'' cast and crew, not least due to his tendency to injure himself/lose teeth in the pursuit of stunts. He's the butt of many jokes by the ''Jackass'' crew, most notably and one of [[Johnny Knoxville]]'s favorite,<ref name=knoxvilleFav>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Marlow|title=Johnny Knoxville: My 6 Favorite ‘Jackass’ Pranks, From 'Terror Taxi' to 'Bad Grandpa'|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/10/25/johnny-knoxville-my-6-favorite-jackass-pranks-from-terror-taxi-to-bad-grandpa.html|website=thedailybeast|accessdate=September 25, 2014|date=25 October 2014}}</ref> the infamous "Terror Taxi" in ''[[Jackass Number Two]]''. In a stunt where Ehren played a terrorist passenger in a [[taxicab]] where he unknowingly wore a "pube beard" made up from the shaved pubic hair of his co-stars.<ref name=knoxvilleFav/>
