'''Konstantina Kouneva''' ({{lang-el|Κωνσταντίνα Κούνεβα}}, born 28 September 1964), also known as '''Kostadinka Kuneva''' ({{lang-bg|Костадинка Кунева}}), is a [[Bulgaria]]n [[immigrant]] in [[Greece]], [[trade union]]ist and secretary of the Greek Trade Union of Cleaners and Housekeepers.<ref name="focus">{{cite web|url=http://www.focus-fen.net/index.php?id=f1819|title=Kuneva case – the most severe assault on trade unionist in Greece for 50 years|work=FOCUS Information Agency}}</ref> She was elected as a [[Member of the European Parliament|MEP]] in the [[European Parliament election, 2014 (Greece)|2014 European Parliament elections]].
==Attack and reactions== Kouneva was working as a [[cleaner]] for the Oikomet company (providing services to [[ISAP]], among other clients, through [[outsourcing]]). She was [[acid throwing| attacked]] with [[sulfuric acid]] (vitriol) on 22 December 2008 and made to swallow it; she lost the sight in one eye and suffered internal organ damage as a result of the attack<ref>[http://www.iht.com/articles/ap/2008/12/30/europe/EU-Bulgaria-Greece-Acid-Attack.php IHT]</ref> <ref> http://news.in.gr/greece/article/?aid=970755 </ref> an event which sparked [[protest]]s<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iww.org.au/node/617|title=Konstantina Kouneva more soli acts + Galeano & Einstein - Industrial Workers of the World|work=iww.org.au|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090531220457/http://www.iww.org.au/node/617|archivedate=2009-05-31|df=}}</ref> and clashes with the [[Greek police]] during [[2008 civil unrest in Greece]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://libcom.org/news/bosses-attack-militant-cleaners-syndicalist-vitriolic-acid-athens-protest-march-occupation-|title=Protesters clash with riot police over acid attack on syndicalist cleaner in Athens|work=libcom.org}}</ref>
The protests, which included [[banner]]s reading ''Konstandinka, you're not alone'', continued at least until 22 January 2009 and numbering 3,000 people, with [[tear gas]] being used by the [[Monades Apokatastasis Taksis|MAT]] police forces.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/greece/4324250/Athens-erupts-in-violence-after-acid-attack-on-immigrant.html|title=Athens erupts in violence after acid attack on immigrant|author=Nick Squires|date=23 January 2009|work=Telegraph.co.uk}}</ref>
The attack was described as the most severe assault on a trade unionist in Greece in 50 years.<ref name="focus"/>
==Education== Kouneva graduated from the [[St. Cyril and St. Methodius University of Veliko Tarnovo]] with a degree in [[History]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Αυγή|date=29 April 2014|accessdate=3 February 2015|url=http://www.avgi.gr/article/2447857/ta-biografika-ton-upopsifion-eurobouleuton-tou-suriza|title=Τα βιογραφικά των υποψήφιων ευρωβουλευτών του ΣΥΡΙΖΑ|language=Greek}}</ref>{{when|date=June 2016}}
==Politics== She was elected to the [[European Parliament]] as a candidate of the left-wing [[Coalition of the Radical Left|SYRIZA]] party in the [[European Parliament election, 2014 (Greece)|European Parliament election]] held on 25 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=επτά ημέρες|date=27 May 2014|accessdate=3 February 2015|url=http://www.7imeres.gr/%CE%BA%CF%89%CE%BD%CF%83%CF%84%CE%B1%CE%BD%CF%84%CE%AF%CE%BD%CE%B1-%CE%BA%CE%BF%CF%8D%CE%BD%CE%B5%CE%B2%CE%B1-%CE%B7-%CE%B9%CF%83%CF%84%CE%BF%CF%81%CE%AF%CE%B1-%CF%84%CE%B7%CF%82-%CE%B1%CF%80%CF%8C/|title=Ποια είναι η Κωνσταντίνα Κούνεβα|language=Greek}}</ref>
