{{Infobox model | name = Yésica Toscanini | image = Yesica Toscanini.jpg | caption = Toscanini at a photo shoot in [[Tucson, Arizona]] | birth_name = Yésica Toscanini | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|3|26}}<ref name="TIFDb" /> | birth_place = [[Junín, Buenos Aires Province|Junín]], [[Argentina]]<ref name="TIFDb" /> | height = {{height|m=1.76|precision=0}} | haircolor = Brown | eyecolor = Brown | agency = Dotto Models - [[Venice]], [[Italy]]<ref name="TIFDb"/> | website = | spouse = }} '''Yésica Toscanini''' ({{IPA-es|ˈʝesika toskaˈnini}}; born 26 March 1986 in [[Junín, Buenos Aires Province|Junín]], [[Argentina]])<ref name="TIFDb" /> is a professional Argentine [[fashion model]].
She appeared in the 2006 and 2007 ''[[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue]]''s.<ref name="si07">[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/features/2007_swimsuit/models/yesica_toscanini/ Sports Illustrated's 2007 Swimsuit Issue], accessed 2007-06-15.</ref><ref name="si06">[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/features/2006_swimsuit/models/yesica_toscanini.html Sports Illustrated's 2006 Swimsuit Issue], accessed 2007-06-15.</ref> She was photographed for the cover of the Argentine edition of [[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] and twice for ''Para Ti'' magazine. She also appeared in the [[Abercrombie & Fitch]] catalog of 2006. She played the high school sweetheart of [[Enrique Iglesias]] in the music video for "[[Do You Know? (The Ping Pong Song)]]".<ref name="pingpong">{{es icon}} [http://www.dottomodels.net/noticias/noticia.php?id=236 VIDEOCLIP DE ENRIQUE IGLESIAS CON YÉSICA TOSCANINI] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071015140613/http://www.dottomodels.net/noticias/noticia.php?id=236 |date=15 October 2007 }}, accessed 2007-11-28.</ref> In 2008 she was selected as the girl for the Intimissimi spring&ndash;summer ad campaign.<ref name="TIFDb">[http://www.tifdb.com/models/yesica_toscanini/532 The Internet Fashion Database] Retrieved and verified on 2009-06-13</ref>
Through legal counsel she requested, and was granted the right, to have all her images and data to be removed from internet search results in Argentina.<ref name="privacy">[https://www.npr.org/blogs/krulwich/2012/02/23/147289169/is-the-right-to-be-forgotten-the-biggest-threat-to-free-speech-on-the-internet NPR, "The Right to be Forgotten"]</ref>
